[Amit Varma]: or Imtiaz Ali.

02:37:11.020 --> 02:37:15.420
[Amit Varma]: I was instead going to ask you about the Raghu Sanjay Lal Jaitley test for alcohol, which

02:37:15.420 --> 02:37:19.980
[Amit Varma]: you mentioned in edition 32, which is a takeoff from the Bechdel test.

02:37:19.980 --> 02:37:23.820
[Amit Varma]: Now the Bechdel test is of course named after Alison Bechdel, the brilliant graphic novelist

02:37:23.820 --> 02:37:27.220
[Amit Varma]: who wrote one of my favorite graphic novels, Fun Home.

02:37:27.220 --> 02:37:31.860
[Amit Varma]: And the Bechdel test is basically a test of gender inequality in fiction and films.

02:37:31.860 --> 02:37:36.680
[Amit Varma]: And the test is that if in a book or a film, there are two women characters speaking to

02:37:36.680 --> 02:37:40.660
[Amit Varma]: each other about something other than a man, you've passed the Bechdel test.

02:37:40.660 --> 02:37:44.420
[Amit Varma]: Now you have something called the Raghu Sanjay Lal Jaitley alcohol test.

02:37:44.420 --> 02:37:45.620
[Guest]: Tell me a bit about that.

02:37:45.620 --> 02:37:51.060
[Guest]: Well, I have to remember now, but I think there were three conditions.

02:37:51.060 --> 02:37:55.660
[Amit Varma]: The alcohol test has to be, I can actually read it out because I've taken the notes.

02:37:55.660 --> 02:37:56.660
[Amit Varma]: So should I do that?

